data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code:

---

**1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree**

Your entire manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` construction is no longer needed. Replace with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The `Action<SetPropertyCalls<Blog>>` signature lets you use normal C# control flow — no expression tree building required.

---

**2. Complex type column names — two changes**

**Same-name properties are now uniquified.** If `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` both exist, EF 10 appends a number to disambiguate (e.g., `Street` and `Street1`). This generates a migration renaming columns.

**Nested complex types use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` now maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` instead of `BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix:** Pin the old column names explicitly so no migration renames occur:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
    {
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
    {
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    {
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
        {
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

---

**3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter**

Every method on this interface now has an additional `string logCommandText` parameter. This contains the redacted SQL (safe for logging). Fix:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← add this
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) with the same additional parameter.
